output:
{
  "summary": "报道概述了近期加剧的巴以暴力冲突，包括多起巴勒斯坦青少年袭击以色列士兵和警察，并遭击毙的事件，指出自2015年10月以来已有大量人员伤亡，且暴力持续没有减少迹象。"
}

{
  "summary": "爱丁堡大学推出新MOOC课程，主题聚焦于苏格兰独立公投。课程从8月25日起开放，涵盖公投背景、网络辩论和视频讲解，并将与其他地区的独立运动进行对比。课程期间还将进行民意调查，以评估课程对参与者投票倾向的影响。"
}

{
  "summary": "The Wanted is enjoying success in the US with their song 'Glad You Came', making them the first UK boy band to reach the top three on the American iTunes chart. The track has sold over 300,000 copies, with success attributed to a combination of sales and airplay on the US charts, and the group feels proud to be part of a wave of British success in America."
}

{
    "summary": "Lee Oates, 49, died six days after an assault. Jack Kent, 21, pleaded guilty to the assault and was sentenced to eight years and four months in prison. The assault occurred after an argument escalated, and the police described Kent's actions as undeniably violent."
}

{
  "summary": "Buckinghamshire council installed child-shaped bollards outside schools in Iver to deter speeding. Two were recently repositioned to face traffic at a resident's request. While the parish council funded them for safety, a local resident called them 'creepy and terrifying.'"
}

{
    "summary": "A new proton beam therapy center is being built in Manchester, set to open in 2018, to treat up to 750 cancer patients annually and employ 160 staff, reducing the need for patients to travel abroad for this advanced treatment."
}

{
  "summary": "An air quality monitoring unit, after 20 years of operation, has identified pollution hotspots. The director proposes introducing air quality standards and possible licensing for industries to ensure compliance and protect residents' health, with a report due by year's end."
}

{
  "summary": "Two separate stabbing incidents occurred in Coventry, leaving a 21-year-old man in life-threatening condition and another man undergoing surgery for multiple wounds. One arrest has been made, and police are investigating to determine if the two incidents are linked, with a cordon in place and local businesses affected."
}

{
    "summary": "Police responded to a report of two viable devices by implementing a public safety operation that closed several roads. The cordons have since been lifted. Authorities thanked the community for their cooperation and urged anyone with information about suspicious activity to come forward."
}

{
  "summary": "A couple, Samantha Gamble and Frankie Byrne, got married at home despite terminal illness and lockdown restrictions, after political intervention allowed the ceremony, which held immense personal significance for them."
}

{
  "summary": "Baljit Singh, 37, was found dead in an alley in Hayes after a neck compression assault. Police are investigating a pre-assault argument, reviewing CCTV, and seeking two men he was with, along with witnesses from the area, with no arrests yet."
}

{
  "summary": "A poll shows Labour leading but with potentially fewer seats in the upcoming Welsh Assembly election. Plaid Cymru is close behind the Conservatives, and UKIP's presence could influence results. Survey data details party support percentages for both constituency and regional list votes, with projections indicating Labour may lose seats compared to 2011."
}

{
    "summary": "一辆旅游大巴在台湾国道转弯处因可能超速失控翻倾，造成44人伤亡，其中32人死亡。该车为赏樱旅游团，乘客多为年长者。事故再次引发对台湾旅游交通安全的担忧。"
}

{
  "summary": "19-year-old Edward Mosley admitted to shooting two nesting herring gulls, an act described as 'callous' by the RSPCA. He was given a four-week curfew and ordered to pay £385 in court costs. The RSPCA reminded the public that gulls are protected under the Wildlife and Countryside Act 1981."
}

{
    "summary": "A three-day agricultural show in Harrogate, now in its 161st year, attracted over 135,000 attendees, featuring livestock competitions, farming exhibitions, and a visit from Prince Andrew. The event director praised its continual improvement, though an incident involving a prize-winning bull resulted in a handler being hospitalized."
}

{
  "summary": "David Newton, a 50-year-old heroin addict, was sentenced to six months in prison for assaulting a nurse and other hospital staff at Arrowe Park Hospital by coughing, spitting, and kicking chairs, amid uncertainty over whether he had COVID-19. He was also ordered to pay £300 in compensation."
}

{
  "summary": "Network Rail closed one of six lines at Manchester Piccadilly station, disrupting services to Birmingham, Manchester Airport, and London, with overnight repair work planned on four lines. Passengers expressed frustration, referencing past timetable issues. Replacement buses and ticket acceptance on alternative services were arranged, and some Virgin trains were cancelled. Passengers were advised to check before traveling."
}

{
  "summary": "The county council plans to reduce engines at five fire stations and close Dalton station to save £24m, citing a 34% drop in incidents and a 69% decrease in fire injuries since 2007/08, but the Fire Brigades Union protests that this will endanger lives."
}

{
  "summary": "The summary describes the separation and complex divorce proceedings of actors Angelina Jolie and Brad Pitt, known as 'Brangelina'. It details their initial meeting, their marriage, the six children, the initial divorce filing citing 'irreconcilable differences', a bitter child custody battle that included allegations against Pitt which were cleared, a custody agreement to avoid trial, and that a final divorce settlement is still pending."
}

{
  "summary": "Two fatal car accidents occurred on a road near Ecclefechan and Kirkpatrick-Fleming, resulting in the deaths of three individuals and serious injuries to three others, causing significant road closures and traffic delays before reopening by midday."
}

{
    "summary": "Police responded to a fight near Birmingham's MAC Centre in Cannon Hill Park, resulting in one arrest for assault on officers and a security guard, and a second teenager hospitalized with a hand injury. Multiple people suffered minor injuries, and police are seeking information from the public."
}

{
  "summary": "Bishop Nicholas Holtam, the first Church of England bishop married to a divorcee due to a synod rule change, gave his inaugural sermon at Salisbury Cathedral, succeeding retired Bishop David Stancliffe. He leads the diocese covering Wiltshire, Dorset, Hampshire, and Devon, with about 1,600 guests at the ceremony, having previously been vicar at St Martin-in-the-Fields in London."
}

{
  "summary": "Police arrested four men as part of a long-running investigation into violent incidents in Irlam and Salford. One incident involved gunshots fired into a car, injuring a man, and another involved a machete attack that critically injured a man. Authorities are urging the public to come forward with any information."
}

{
  "summary": "文章描述了西斯廷礼拜堂在教皇选举期间的严格保密措施和选举程序，包括烟囱冒烟的颜色代表选举结果、选举期间的隔离与通讯管制，以及投票过程。"
}

{
  "summary": "Maria Alyokhina, imprisoned for a controversial protest performance against Putin, protested via video link that her rights were violated and refused further remote participation. Her bandmate Nadezhda Tolokonnikova previously had parole denied, while a third member had her sentence suspended. Their prosecution drew international condemnation."
}

{
  "summary": "Minister David Cretney acknowledged issues with late-running and unreliable buses, particularly during rain, which can cause leaks and electrical failures. New replacement buses are scheduled for June, and service disruptions are prioritized for school transport during peak times."
}

{
  "summary": "The text describes efforts to revive Ullamaliztli, an ancient Mesoamerican ball game with deep cultural and religious significance that was banned by Spanish conquistadors. A recent tournament featured modern rules with teams using their hips to hit a rubber ball, diverging from the ancient practice of sacrificing losing players."
}

{
  "summary": "Dalian Wanda Group, backed by Chinese billionaire Wang Jianlin, is acquiring the Gold Fields House office building in Sydney for A$415 million to develop a luxury hotel, residential, and retail complex. This is part of Wanda's recent global expansion, which includes investments in London and Madrid hotels, a significant stake in Spanish football club Atletico Madrid, and ownership of US and UK assets. The announcement boosted Dalian Wanda Commercial Properties' shares by 3.4%."
}

{
  "summary": "Guernsey politicians are debating whether to deregulate Sunday trading. Deputy Al Brouard opposes the move, arguing it would eliminate a day of rest. Deputy Barry Brehaut supports allowing shops to open, believing the market would find a natural balance. A public consultation will be held, and if supported, the law could change within a year."
}

{
  "summary": "The text summarizes a literary awards ceremony in Wales, recognizing winners in both English and Welsh languages across categories like poetry and fiction. It mentions specific winners, judges, and the event's organizational transition."
}

{
  "summary": "The article discusses the Brexit trade negotiations, highlighting that Boris Johnson's rhetoric is not merely messaging for the EU but indicates a serious preparation for a potential no-deal outcome, as talks have stalled despite a deal being mutually beneficial. A last-minute change of heart remains possible."
}

{
  "summary": "Sri Lankan politician Mangala Samaraweera argues that for Sri Lanka to restore its international reputation, the government must take concrete legal action against media outlets like Channel4 that aired alleged war crimes footage, rather than just verbally denying the allegations. He suggests obtaining forensic video expert certification to challenge the footage in international court."
}

{
  "summary": "Joanna Simons, the chief executive, will be made redundant in June as part of a council plan to protect frontline services and adapt to expected government austerity measures, shifting away from traditional management towards a more devolved decision-making structure."
}

{
  "summary": "The storm Ernesto, now with winds of 110 km/h, hit Mexico's Yucatan Peninsula and made landfall again near Coatzacoalcos, Veracruz, after affecting several Central American countries. It has caused coastal flooding, prompted the preparation of thousands of shelters, and put 11 states on alert. The storm is expected to weaken inland, and while oil installations in the key port of Coatzacoalcos were monitored, no disruptions were reported, though the port was closed as a precaution."
}

{
  "summary": "新华社报道中国军方高级官员殷方龙强调坚持党对军队的绝对领导，警惕'军队非党化'言论。此言论紧随此前关于副总参谋长章沁生因支持'军队国家化'而被停职调查的传闻。"
}

{
  "summary": "Actor Michael Le Vell, who plays Kevin Webster in the soap 'Coronation Street', was arrested following an allegation of a historical offence, which he strenuously denies and vows to prove his innocence. He was released on bail pending further inquiries."
}

{
  "summary": "South Marston Distribution (SDC) is cutting 370 temporary jobs, representing 38% of its workforce, due to Honda reducing production at a nearby plant. Since over 95% of SDC's work is for Honda, this decision directly responds to Honda's earlier announcement of cutting 800 jobs at its Swindon plant because of weak European demand. A consultation process is now underway."
}

{
  "summary": "An anonymous person or group erected an 8ft 'Bristoland' sign on a steep gorge overlooking Bristol, reminiscent of the Hollywood sign. The playful, spontaneous act, likely requiring climbing gear, was intended to make people smile and is being celebrated by a local urban art festival."
}

{
  "summary": "The Centre for Contemporary Arts (CCA) in Glasgow, which had been closed since a fire in June, is beginning to reopen. The cafe-bar, bookshop, and retail space will reopen on a Saturday, followed by exhibitions and performances on the following Tuesday. The reopening is crucial as prolonged closure threatened funding and the jobs of the centre's staff and many freelancers."
}

{
  "summary": "A rare Slavonian grebe, a 'red-listed' species with only 30 UK breeding pairs, has been sighted at a restored nature reserve in Rhyl, Denbighshire, north Wales, where it is being monitored."
}

{
  "summary": "Conwy and Anglesey councils in Wales are increasing council tax by 5% and 4.8% respectively to address budget shortfalls. Conwy faces a £6m shortfall due to reduced Welsh Government grants and higher wages, and will make service cuts and use reserves. Anglesey, with a £2.5m gap, aims to protect services despite the increase. The rise translates to about £50 extra per year for a typical Band D property on Anglesey."
}

{
  "summary": "Welsh officials Stephen Crabb and another speaker emphasized the historic significance of an upcoming summit in Wales for attracting global attention, boosting investment, and promoting tourism, urging future momentum from this event."
}

{
  "summary": "Ryanair is expanding significantly at London Southend Airport, operating over 50 weekly flights and expecting to carry one million passengers annually on 13 routes. This expansion establishes their 14th UK base, creating direct aviation jobs and supporting many ancillary positions. The move supports the airport's ambitious growth target for passenger numbers by 2022, despite Ryanair's noted status as one of Europe's top polluters."
}

{
  "summary": "A 52-year-old prison officer was murdered while driving to work, marking the first such death in Northern Ireland in nearly 20 years. His funeral condemned the killers. Police have made a fourth arrest in the investigation, following three earlier arrests which have since been released."
}

{
  "summary": "Conservative Brexiteer Jacob Rees-Mogg asserted on BBC NI's The View that the Irish border will remain open because both the UK and Irish governments have stated they do not want a hard border. He argued that only a sovereign state can decide to police its border, and with neither government willing to implement controls, no 'phantom government' will do so. He also dismissed the need for a personal visit to the border region to understand Brexit's impact, stating that physical infrastructure is unnecessary and a visit wouldn't provide further insight."
}

{
  "summary": "哈里王子与来自多国的12名伤残军人共同完成南极300公里徒步慈善行，旨在凸显受伤军人的需求和成就，并为他们的再培训筹款，原计划的竞赛因恶劣天气取消。"
}

{
  "summary": "A Polish man, Pawel Kwik, was banned from driving for 22 months and fined after admitting to drink driving. He was found on a motorway, initially suspected of having a cardiac arrest, but was arrested. Police expressed relief that no one was seriously injured and noted the danger posed to public helpers."
}

{
    "summary": "Cheryl Cole has cancelled her work commitments for a week due to medical advice, following reported exhaustion and gastroenteritis that led to her collapsing at a photoshoot. This comes amid a busy schedule that includes judging on 'The X Factor', touring with Black Eyed Peas, recording her solo album, and upcoming performances, all following her divorce from Ashley Cole earlier in the year."
}

{
  "summary": "Darren Cumberbatch died after being detained by police. His body had unexplained injuries, and his family alleges a Taser was used. An independent investigation into the circumstances, including police use of force, is ongoing, preventing further comment from officers until its conclusion."
}

{
  "summary": "Local residents have complained to North Wales Police about motorbikes and mopeds illegally using a promenade lane, which is dangerous and a nuisance. Police are urging the public to report registration numbers of offending vehicles and have implemented a dispersal order to prevent groups from drinking in the area."
}

{
  "summary": "Recent extreme weather has caused damage to the Somerset Levels, impacting agriculture and wildlife. A partnership of local stakeholders is calling for a coordinated water management plan, but funding issues have historically been a barrier. The government's environmental department is conducting an urgent review to find solutions."
}

{
  "summary": "An 18-year-old girl, Millie Taylor-Noonan, was killed after being hit by a car. Separately, a 16-year-old girl died after being hit by a lorry, and a 14-year-old was injured."
}

{
  "summary": "For the second time in three nights, a cable problem caused a power outage on the islands. Power was restored after about 50 minutes, though some isolated low-voltage issues remained. The electricity companies are investigating the failure after assurances of a secure supply proved incorrect."
}

{
  "summary": "A resident in Hartlepool witnessed a truck explosion, caused by two masked men who fled in a light-colored vehicle. No one was injured, but there was significant property damage. Police are seeking witnesses."
}

{
  "summary": "A Singaporean tourist, Lon Lee Alle, was severely bitten by a venomous Komodo dragon in Indonesia while ignoring warnings and taking pictures too close during its feeding. Park officials emphasized it was the first incident in five years, stressing never to stay with locals without official guidance when visiting Komodo dragon spaces for budget cuts. After the bite, Alle was evacuated by official transport and is now under treatment with hospital resources available for recovery."
}

{
  "summary": "Three swans, one shot in the head, were found injured in Windsor, believed to be from an air gun. They are receiving treatment, and police are investigating the incident, appealing for public information."
}

{
    "summary": "In June, two young osprey chicks hatched in the Lake District to a new breeding pair. The male chick has already fledged and was seen flying with its parents, while the female is nearly ready to fledge. This marks a significant conservation success as ospreys have returned to the area since 2001 after a 150-year absence. The site is protected by over 100 volunteers and attracts many visitors, with live nest footage available to the public."
}

{
  "summary": "Andrew Culture expressed disappointment that plans for a new Ipswich arts centre excluded live music provisions, highlighting a long-standing need for a mid-sized venue. He launched a website to gather public ideas and foster discussion about creating a venue similar to those in Norwich and Colchester."
}

{
    "summary": "This year's Bafta Cymru awards ceremony is being held online due to the pandemic and will be hosted by Alex Jones. His Dark Materials leads with nine nominations, while Sir Anthony Hopkins is nominated for best actor. Veteran Leslie Dilley will receive an outstanding contribution award, and the event highlights both established nominees like Russell T Davies and first-time nominees in categories covering craft, performance, and production."
}

{
  "summary": "A new play park in Worcester commemorates Cromwell's crossing before the 1651 Battle of Worcester. The design includes symbolic references like mounds representing boats and wooden weaponry, blending recreation with historical education. Local officials and historical societies are planning events, including re-enactments, to mark the battle's 360th anniversary, highlighting ongoing efforts to honor this historical event."
}

{
  "summary": "Richard Scott, Duke of Buccleuch and Queensberry, has been appointed to the Order of the Thistle, Scotland's highest chivalry order, effective from 2017. As one of only 16 knights, he will also serve as the Queen's representative to the Church of Scotland's assembly in 2018, coinciding with Prince Harry's wedding."
}

{
  "summary": "A documentary series filmed in the Hebrides aims to boost tourism in the region, following the success of previous TV programs like 'Island Parish' and 'Balamory' which significantly increased visitor numbers. The VisitScotland chairman highlights the show's potential to promote Scotland's natural beauty and its influence on tourism."
}

{
    "summary": "A student finance calculator created by BBC News uses averages and assumptions about future UK economic conditions and individual incomes to illustrate potential loan repayment costs under various scenarios, not to provide precise individual predictions. It includes downloadable data and a customizable spreadsheet. Key contributors are acknowledged."
}

{
  "summary": "Three men from Essex pleaded guilty to burglary after police stopped their van. They crashed through a barrier at a construction site in Hatfield Peverel to steal property. The court sentenced them to community service: Johnnie Scamp to 100 hours, and James Scamp and Thomas Simmonds to 140 hours each."
}

{
"summary": "Ron Hogg, a former police and crime commissioner in Durham diagnosed with motor neurone disease, has posthumously been awarded a CBE for his charitable and political services. Colleagues praised him as universally liked and respected, with decades of dedicated public service that touched thousands of lives, noting the honour is a fitting tribute to his legacy."
}

{
    "summary": "A public consultation is starting for a 10-year, £500 million development plan called Birmingham Smithfield. The 14-hectare project will transform the city centre site of the old wholesale markets into a mixed-use area featuring Festival Square, parks, gardens, cafes, shops, restaurants, a new building for the retail markets, 2,000 new homes, and is expected to create 3,000 jobs."
}

{
  "summary": "缅甸因持续豪雨引发全国性水灾，已致27人死亡，四个行政区进入紧急状态。约14万人在若开邦避难，交通受阻，50多万亩农田被淹。联合国将派小组评估灾区需求。"
}

{
  "summary": "The UK government canceled its £1 billion carbon capture storage competition, affecting the Peterhead and White Rose projects. This decision, criticized as wrong by Scottish First Minister Nicola Sturgeon, ends funding that could have created many jobs, disappointing the involved companies and local politicians."
}

{
  "summary": "Resumen sobre Suárez y otros detenidos por fraude en el IGSS relacionados con contratos de servicios médicos otorgados a empresas no cualificadas, así como las protestas contra la corrupción en Guatemala y la dimisión de la vicepresidenta Baldetti."
}

{
  "summary": "El 11 de septiembre de 2011, una roca de media tonelada impactó la Luna, creando un destello visible desde la Tierra durante ocho segundos y dejando un cráter de 40 metros de ancho, según un estudio publicado en 'Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society'."
}

{
  "summary": "Esta es la primera vez que el presidente sirio Bashar al-Assad envía un mensaje directo al Papa Francisco desde el inicio de la guerra civil en 2011, expresando su determinación de defender a los sirios de los islamistas radicales y afirmando que el conflicto debe resolverse mediante un diálogo nacional sin injerencia extranjera. Por su parte, el Papa Francisco ha hecho numerosos llamados para poner fin al conflicto, que ha causado más de 100,000 muertes desde 2011."
}

{
  "summary": "En Gao, Mali, manifestantes protestaron contra rumores de un plan estadounidense que, según ellos, favorecería a rebeldes tuareg, lanzando piedras y artefactos incendiarios contra una base de la ONU (Minusma). Los soldados de la ONU respondieron con gases lacrimógenos, y algunos testigos los acusaron de disparar. La misión de la ONU de unos 10,000 soldados fue desplegada hace casi dos años tras una intervención francesa para evitar que rebeldes islamistas tomaran la capital."
}

{
    "summary": "La manifestación 'Inunda Wall Street', no autorizada, tiene lugar antes de la cumbre climática de la ONU para protestar contra la contribución del capitalismo al cambio climático. Los organizadores planean bloquear el acceso a la Bolsa de Nueva York. Esta sigue a una marcha masiva que reunió a 310,000 personas el día anterior."
}

{
    "summary": "Tras 20 años de aceptar mujeres sacerdotes, la Iglesia Anglicana, a pesar de la oposición tradicionalista, podría aprobar la ordenación de mujeres obispo este año, dada la creencia en suficiente apoyo e incluidas concesiones como la opción de un obispo masculino alternativo, lo que reforzaría el estatus de las mujeres dentro de la jerarquía eclesiástica."
}

{
  "summary": "El Vaticano nombra una comisión investigadora para reformar su banco interno (Instituto para las Obras de Religión) ante sospechas de lavado de dinero y falta de transparencia."
}

{
  "summary": "Un adolescente cayó accidentalmente en el recinto de un tigre blanco en peligro de extinción en un hotel, fue atacado por el animal y testigos intentaron ayudarlo lanzando objetos. El incidente ocurrió en India, donde habita esta rara subespecie de tigre."
}

{
  "summary": "89岁的穆加贝以绝对优势赢得大选并开始第七次连任，其主要对手茨万吉拉伊指控选举舞弊但被法院驳回，拒绝出席就职典礼，典礼现场气氛热烈。"
}

{
  "summary": "Después de que Hezbolá matara a dos soldados israelíes y, en respuesta, Israel matara a un pacificador español, Israel confirmó haber recibido un mensaje del Líbano a través de la misión de la ONU UNIFIL. Las fuerzas israelíes están en alerta y se reportan aviones sobrevolando la frontera. El ataque de Hezbolá fue posiblemente una represalia por un ataque aéreo israelí en Siria que mató a un general iraní y a miembros de Hezbolá."
}

{
    "summary": "Manifestantes marchan en Caracas desde Plaza Venezuela hacia el Ministerio Público para exigir la liberación de estudiantes arrestados en Táchira. Es la protesta opositora más grande desde las elecciones de abril. Hay tensión ante posibles enfrentamientos al acercarse a zonas consideradas bastiones del gobierno."
}

{
    "summary": "No se conoce al responsable del lanzamiento de un cohete Katyusha cerca de la frontera israelí-libanesa. Aunque Israel respondió con patrullas, no hubo más hostilidades. En el contexto de alta tensión por la guerra en Siria, es improbable que Hezbolá, ocupado apoyando al gobierno sirio, haya realizado el ataque para no provocar a Israel."
}

{
  "summary": "Las dos Coreas reiniciaron negociaciones para reunir familias separadas por la guerra y tienen discrepancias sobre reanudar el turismo en Kumgang, con el Norte queriendo vincular ambos asuntos y el Sur manteniendo que son separados."
}

{
  "summary": "El gobierno de Venezuela atribuye la escasez y las largas filas por productos básicos a 'opositores infiltrados' y revendedores, implementando restricciones horarias para las filas. Los analistas críticos señalan como causas el control de cambios, la regulación de precios y la caída de los ingresos petroleros, mientras que el presidente Maduro lo denuncia como una 'emboscada' de la oligarquía."
}

{
  "summary": "La madre de Óscar Alberto Martínez Ramírez relata el doloroso momento de su despedida cuando él y su pequeña hija emprendieron un viaje desde El Salvador hacia Estados Unidos, expresando su amor y esperanzas antes de que partieran en busca del 'sueño americano'."
}

{
    "summary": "Un terremoto de magnitud 8,2 sacudió el norte de Chile. Una mujer murió por una caída. Las provincias de Arica, Parinacota y Tarapacá fueron declaradas zona de catástrofe. La alerta de tsunami fue levantada y se ha reestablecido hasta la mitad del suministro eléctrico."
}

{
  "summary": "El fiscal general de Irlanda del Norte, John Larkin, propuso que no se investiguen más los asesinatos ocurridos antes del Acuerdo de Viernes Santo de 1998, incluidos los cometidos por paramilitares, la policía o el ejército, argumentando que es una consecuencia lógica del acuerdo, no una amnistía formal. Esta propuesta se presenta mientras se negocia cómo manejar el pasado del conflicto."
}

{
  "summary": "El Banco de España reportó una contracción económica similar a la del trimestre anterior para el tercer trimestre, aunque las condiciones financieras adversas se estaban atenuando ligeramente. La demanda nacional cayó un 1,2%, amortiguada por la anticipación del gasto ante la subida del IVA y el plan de pago a proveedores."
}

{
  "summary": "El presidente Obama, en un acto por el Día de la Independencia, elogió a los inmigrantes como parte fundamental de la identidad de EE.UU., mientras critica la inacción del Congreso en la reforma migratoria y anuncia que tomará medidas ejecutivas para abordar la crisis en la frontera sur, causada por la llegada de miles de inmigrantes indocumentados, incluidos menores."
}

{
    "summary": "Identificación de Mohamed Aggad, de 23 años, como el tercer atacante en los ataques de París del 13 de noviembre, donde 130 personas murieron, incluyendo casi 90 en el Bataclan. Los otros dos atacantes fueron Omar Ismail Mostefai y Samy Amimour, y el Estado Islámico reivindicó la autoría."
}

{
  "summary": "Toyota proyecta un beneficio neto de US$9.700 millones hasta marzo de 2013 debido a la recuperación de ventas en Japón y EE.UU., con un incremento del 221% en el trimestre julio-septiembre. Sin embargo, muestra cautela por posibles afectaciones debido a la disputa territorial con China y la crisis en Europa."
}

{
  "summary": "Líderes religiosos como el papa Francisco, el Dalai Lama y el arzobispo Desmond Tutu rindieron homenaje a Nelson Mandela tras su fallecimiento a los 95 años. Reconocieron su ejemplo como promotor de la dignidad humana, su transformación personal y su legado, rezando e instando a que inspire a Sudáfrica a luchar por la justicia y el bien común."
}

{
  "summary": "Jay Carney, vocero de la Casa Blanca, cuestiona la afirmación de la investigadora de la ONU Carla del Ponte de que hay pruebas de que los rebeldes sirios usaron armas químicas (gas sarín). Carney sugiere que es más probable que el gobierno sirio las haya usado. Del Ponte basa su sospecha en testimonios, pero reconoce que no hay evidencias irrefutables y que se necesita más investigación."
}

{
